    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"347475\">Bjørn Kjos-Hanssen ☀️</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/113489-new-members/topic/Help.20with.20modular.20arithmetic.20using.20.22sub_modEq_zero.22/near/472756765\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>This works:</p>\n<p><div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Algebra</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">ModEq</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">p</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℤ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">p</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≡</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">PMOD</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">6</span><span class=\"o\">])</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">p</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≡</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">PMOD</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">6</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">AddCommGroup</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">sub_modEq_zero</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">mpr</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h0</span>\n</code></pre></div><br>\n</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>This works indeed! Thank you so much! It turns out that a key thing to watch out for is the difference between <strong>integer arithmetic (<code>ℤ</code>)</strong> and <strong>natural number arithmetic (<code>ℕ</code>)</strong> in Lean - the hypothesis (p : Nat) is not compatible with the theorem <code>sub_modEq_zero</code>.</p>",
